name: melakufendika
description:
Melaku Belay is an Ethiopian traditional dancer born at Addis Abeba in 1980. He is a free spirit, who has refused to restraint himself in an imposed and academic "traditional" style. As a self-taught dancer, he has taken his inspiration inside the Ethiopian society itself, and among the bearers of the tradition. Throughout his carrier, he has tried to create and develop his own style according to his own experiences and researches through his country, with a touch of improvisation and fantasy.
Melaku is also "a cultural entrepreneur" trying to support and develop the cultural and musical wealth of his country. Since 2008, he is managing one of the most famous Azmari place in Addis Abeba, the Fendika by introducing an innovative idea to his traditional setting. Indeed, during the special events which regularly occurred in Fendika, he has invited many guests, from both Ethiopian and foreign spheres, creating a place which offers a symbiosis between tradition and modernity.

description:
PMC-Ethiopia began working in Ethiopia in 2001. The annual population growth rate is 2.85 percent, which left unchanged would result in a doubling of the population in 25 years.
Ethiopia has made great strides in a number of development areas in the more than a decade PMC-Ethiopia has been working there. According to 2011 Demographic and Health Survey,
the contraceptive prevalence rate in Ethiopia has doubled in the past five years. A variety of PMC programs have worked to help increase knowledge about family planning, contraception, HIV/AIDS, and a number of other issues, such as improving the use of the health extension worker program. PMC-Ethiopia has also won a number of recognition, including the 2011 Global Media Award. The PMC-Ethiopia team is committed to making a difference.

name: Amhara Tourism
description: Amhara Tourism showcases promote tourist attractions, services in the region/ destinations.The Amhara National Region offers an abundance of endemic wildlife opportunities, astonishing diversity of landscapes, historical heritages and religious and cultural festivals. Among the best tourist attractions:-  The 12th century Rock-Hewn churches of Lalibela, and the palaces in Gondar the world known heritages of the country. The traditional mural paintings and hand craft, the preserved corpse of the royality found in the ancient monastries in Lake Tana, as well as the Semien mountains national park, which shelters the endemic Walia ibex, Chilada baboon and Lamergeyer are spectacular tourist attractions, three tourist attractions found in the region are registered in the UNESCO list of world heritages. Besides these known heritages, the Blue Nile Falls, the caves and unique stones in northern Showa, and the Merto Le Mariam church are special tourist attractions’.

From the 1990s onwards, the integrated development approach of World Vision’s Area Programmes (APs) has ensured empowering, sustainable and transformational development across the nation. World Vision is currently delivering change for children through 57 area programs and a number of emergency and humanitarian responses, in partnership with the government, the community, faith-based organizations and other stakeholders throughout Ethiopia.

name: Khaabba - ካባ
description:
Welcome to KHAABBA's YouTube Channel!

KHAABBA is coined from the initials of my family members' names! In Amharic "ካባ" signifies the honorary traditional costume that represents nobility, highness and achievement. That being the name, KHAABBA is a family-owned language service company. The language services at KHAABBA include translation, editing, proofreading, teaching/tutoring of multiple languages, English and Amharic being the major languages at the current stage. Its ambition is to be a hub for services in all Ethiopian languages and other languages of Africa and the world.

In this Youtube channel, the owner aims to also share whatever skills and experiences he assumes to be useful for you out there, including teaching the Amharic language. 

Your comments and feedback are much appreciated and will help KHAABBA to grow!

Support us by becoming a member on Patron: https://www.patreon.com/learnamharicandenglishwithkhaabba.

Thank you and please subscribe! Be a family!

Rocks & Rockhounding

You have to admit, deep down, we all instinctively love rocks. After all, we're only here now because our ancestors successfully used their knowledge of rocks to survive. And still, today, we rely on rocks for nearly everything in life - you're now using and looking at what was once a bunch of rocks to watch these rocks. 

There's so much to learn, and you should know which rocks are dangerous, illegal, or valuable! You have all these rocks in your pocket, everywhere, forever. And, most you can bring home! 

This addiction began with the idea to collect the elements, influence from family, and inspiration from great science/rockhounding videos by incredible creators (in the channels tab). All blame belongs to them for both you being here now, and for fostering the passion to share with you some science and rocks.

description:
Creating extraordinary experiences in extraordinary places.

We, the founders of Safarious, Michael Lorentz, James Kydd and Warren Pearson have over eight decades of collective guiding experience and industry relationships to create meaningful travel experiences, benefitting local communities, wildlife and conservation initiatives as much as it enriches the traveller; and being perpetually curious by nature, we never stop exploring. name: Ethioameri
description:
EthioAmeri, the dynamic digital creator behind an exciting YouTube channel that captures the essence of Ethiopian and American cultures. EthioAmeri is a passionate content creator who skillfully combines our Ethiopian heritage with our experiences as an American to deliver a unique and captivating content to our viewers.

Through our YouTube channel, EthioAmeri takes you on a virtual journey, sharing fascinating insights into Ethiopian traditions, customs, and delicious cuisine. Our deep connection to their Ethiopian roots shines through as they expertly showcase the vibrant culture, breathtaking landscapes, and the rich history of Ethiopia.

At the same time, EthioAmeri effortlessly bridges the gap between Ethiopia and America, offering a fresh perspective on the blending of these two diverse cultures. Whether it's exploring American cities, discussing cultural exchange, or sharing personal stories of navigating life in both countries.

The Gurage people (ጉራጌ) are semitic people speaking the Gurage languages ( sebat bet , soddo kistane , Dobi , Meakan) inhabiting  traditionally inhabit a fertile, semi-mountainous region in central Ethiopia, about 125 kilometers southwest of Addis Ababa. They also inhabit in Adis Ababa, Oromiya region ,Diredawa and Harar.
Most of the Gurage people living outside their regions are known for their hard working trading activities.
     For many reasons, it is seen that the Gurage people is losing their identity. That is why creating this channel is needed. In our programs in future we try to bring cultural renaissance of this culurally rich people.

211CHECK is a fact-checking and information verification platform that works on countering misinformation and disinformation in South Sudan.

211CHECK is managed and run by DEFYHATENOW South Sudan, an NGO registered in South Sudan with a registration number 2285.

DEFYHATENOW works on creating frameworks for enhancing trust between stakeholders in Africa through mobilizing civic action against all forms of hate speech, misinformation, human rights violations, and incitement to violence. The organization is considered one of the leading entities that work on providing data-driven solutions to the problem of hate speech, fake news, and misinformation in Africa, working at the nexus of technology, peacebuilding, and human rights. #defyhatenow’s team of researchers, designers, data analysts, and programmers have a wide range of experiences and are currently leading flagship projects in Ethiopia, Sudan, South Sudan, Cameroon, and Kenya.

name: Addisaba Tube
description:
Addis Ababa (Amharic: አዲስ አበባ, Addis Abäba IPA: , ("new flower") or Addis Abeba, also the capital and largest city of Ethiopia. According to the 2007 census, the city has a population of 2,739,551 inhabitants.
As a chartered city, It is where the African Union is headquartered and where its predecessor the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) was based. It also hosts the headquarters of the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa (ECA), as well as various other continental and international organizations. Addis Ababa is therefore often referred to as "the political capital of Africa" for its historical, diplomatic and political significance for the continent. The city lies a few miles west of the East African Rift which splits Ethiopia into two, through the Nubian Plate and the Somali Plate.

name: Admas University
description:
Admas University was established in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, in October of 1998. Identifying a need for higher education in Somaliland, Admas University established a campus in Hargeisa in September of 2006. The Hargeisa campus was established in line with a greater policy of expanding access to education throughout the region. So far, branch campuses have also been established in Debreseit, Dessie, and Adwa. Since then the university has produced more than 10,000 graduates in various professional fields. Currently the Ethiopian Ministry of Education has accredited all of the University’s Certificate, Diploma and Degree programs. 
At present, the total of enrolled Admas University students is over 10,000 students in all campuses, including the Hargeisa campus. The Hargeisa campus is an autonomous branch that offers Degrees Post Graduate Diploma in various fields.

description:
Ertugrul የተሠኘውን ታሪክ በ አማርኛ አቅርበንላችኋል  #የአርማው ትርጉም

ካይላር ( ካይ ቦዩ )የቱርክ ጎሳ የመጣው ከኦጉዝ ሕዝቦች ሲሆን ከቦዙክ የጎሳ ፌዴሬሽኖች ቅርንጫፎች አንዱ ነው ፡፡

 “ካይ” የሚለው ቃል ኃይል እና ስልጣን ያለው ሰው ማለት ነው ፡፡

በ 15 ኛው ክፍለዘመን እንደተፃፉት የከይ ጎሳ " የኦቶማን ግዛት መስራች “ኡስማን ኢብኑ አል-ጋዚ ፣ አርጦግሩል ኢብኑ ሱለይማን ሻህ ”  እንደነበር ይገመታል፡፡

 በሰማያዊ ሰንደቅ ላይ በነጭ ቀለም የተቀባው የጎሳ አርማ ማለት ጋሻና ሁለት ቀስቶች ማለት ነው-ጋሻው የካይ ተዋጊን ጡንቻ(ጥንካሬ) ነው ፣ እና ሁለቱ ቀስቶች አንድ ለጠላት አንዱ ደግሞ ለከሃዲ ናቸው ፡፡  እንዲሁም ትልቁን ጭልፊት “ንስር” ን ያመለክታል ፡፡

 በዘመናዊ ቱርክኛ “አይ ዋይ አይ” የሚለው ቃል “ጥሩ” ወይም ጥሩ ነገር ማለት ነው ፡፡

 የካይ ጎሳ የእስልምና ሃይማኖት ተከታዮች ሲሆኑ በከባድ ተጋድሎ ተዋጊዎቹም ይታወቃል ፡፡  ካይ በእስልምና ታሪክ ውስጥ በጣም ታዋቂ መሪዎችን አፍርታለች ለምሳሌ የቁስጥንጥንያ ድል አድራጊ ሱልጣን ሙሐመድ አል ፋቲህ (አላህ ይዘንለት )፣  እና ሱልጣን ሱሌማን አልቃኑኒ ይገኙበታል።

BBC አማርኛ NEWS aims to promote Ethiopian and other African countries values, cultures and traditions globally. name: Good Morning Sheger ሸገር
description:
Addis Ababa (Amharic: አዲስ አበባ,  "new flower"), also known as Sheger ‘ሸገር’ is the capital and largest city of Ethiopia. According to the 2007 census, the city has a population of 2,739,551 inhabitants. . It is where the African Union is headquartered and where its predecessor the Organisation of African Unity (OAU) was based. It also hosts the headquarters of the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa (ECA), as well as various other continental and international organizations. Addis Ababa is therefore often referred to as "the political capital of Africa" for its historical, diplomatic and political significance for the continent. The city lies a few miles west of the East African Rift which splits Ethiopia into two, between the Nubian Plate and the Somali Plate. It is home to Addis Ababa University.

Abyssinia sound Band has been established in the year2005 and now obtained 15 years’ experience as one of the renowned musical bands. While he is one of the renowned musicians in Ethiopia; he is typically known for his works as composer, melody and lyrics writer and also as a recording artist.

name: FSD Ethiopia
description:
Financial Sector Deepening Ethiopia (FSD Ethiopia) is a development agency that aims to support the development of accessible, inclusive, and sustainable financial markets for economic growth and development. We take a market systems approach to promote systemic change in Ethiopia’s financial sector.

Funded by Foreign, Commonwealth & Development and the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, we provide technical assistance, grants and research and insights to market actors in both public and private sector domains. Our role is to identify the underlying causes of financial system failures, facilitate market actors to address these constraints, and help build a functional and effective sector that generates economic gains for a wide cross-section of Ethiopian individuals and businesses.

Our vision is to contribute to a thriving financial system that delivers real value to the economy and people of Ethiopia.

description:
In 2012, I decided to photograph a book about the Jewish people to understand how they were impacted over the time of exile, to show how all people are the same and the differences are created by circumstances. Over the course of the next year, I travelled to six continents and 32 countries to show the Jewish people, their impact on the countries where they were allowed to settle and the impacts of those countries on Jewish people and ultimately Israel.

The project ended up having a profound impact on my life. It was a journey of a lifetime and here I share what happened, what I learned and the stories of the people I met. 

Enjoy, subscribe, comment, share and spread the love.

Peace through understanding.

description:
The Medicolegal & Ethics Society of Ethiopia (MESE) is a not-for-profit professional society, registered by Civil Societies Organization Agency (CSOA). Founded in April 2021, the MESE emerged from a need for health, legal professionals & other interested associates to work together to improve medicolegal & ethical knowledge, and promote patient safety through advocacy, education, research and supporting the system. 

The MESE also address the right to health and other related fundamental human rights, with special consideration given to specific groups such as women, children, persons with disabilities, migrants, persons living with HIV/AIDS and marginalized ones, by supporting the state and other stakeholders to take steps to realize the right to health, and by monitoring the right to health and demand accountability at the national level.

name: Akaso Akaso
description:
Akaso is a Belgian fashion label and co-creation concept uniting African artists and Belgian designers.  Every print in the Akaso collection is designed by the Kara tribe in Ethiopia, known for their body painting art.  The Akaso founder took two awarded Belgian designers into Ethiopia, where they worked with six young artists of the Kara Tribe.  The Kara are Africa's smallest and most authentic tribal people.
Every print is an exact reproduction of the original design as created by a Kara tribe artist either on their body or on paper.

The Akaso founder is also the father of two Ethiopian born daughters, and from the discovery of a book on African body painting art, he developed the Akaso vision.  With Akaso he intends to bring African artists to the design table, providing them a window where they can share their stories.  The Kara tribe artists are paid as Western free lance designers.

name: Ms Zelly
description: Zelly Lisanework is an Ethiopian born British writer, poet, multidisciplinary artist, and human rights activist. She is also one of the co-founders of House of Guramayle, a global Ethiopian LGBTQ+ Human Rights organisation. Her work tries to make sense of the injustices in the world whilst also celebrating the beauty to be found, she explores the depths and intersections of marginalised identities and the impact of wider society in everyday life through the lens of neurodiversity, gender, sexuality, nature, mental health and human rights. Her interviews and appearances include local BBC Television and Radio, The Asmara-Addis Literary Festival, Spill Festival of Performance, Folk East Festival, Primadonna Festival, Suffolk Pride, Norwich Pride, London Pride and UK Black Pride.

name: Partners in Ethiopia
description:
Partners in Ethiopia (PIE) is a team of Canadian volunteers working to improve education, community health and maternal health services in Ethiopia with our registered Ethiopian non-profit partner Vision for Bright Future (VBF). We are a secular, non-profit, volunteer-run, charitable organization working to enact effective, compassionate development and aid. 

We proudly operate as a project of Rose Charities Canada whom we entrust to accept donations on our behalf, issue tax receipts and support us administratively very efficiently.  Thus 95+% of your donation goes to the direct project costs in Ethiopia.

Our mostly Enderby, BC-based team includes key people from Partners in the Horn of Africa (PiHA) who are inspired to continue the John Baigent model for development aid now that PiHA has wound down after John's passing. VBF and our Ethiopian communities play key roles in selecting and implementing their projects and contribute 10-20% of the cost of infrastructure projects.

Ethiopia 

country of burnt faces; the Greek word by which the Hebrew Cush is rendered ( Genesis 2:13 ; 2 Kings 19:9 ; Esther 1:1 ; Job 28:19 ; Psalms 68:31 ; 87:4 ), a country which lay to the south of Egypt, beginning at Syene on the First Cataract ( Ezekiel 29:10 ; 30:6 ), and extending to beyond the confluence of the White and Blue Nile. It corresponds generally with what is now known as the Soudan (i.e., the land of the blacks). This country was known to the Hebrews, and is described in Isaiah 18:1 ; Zephaniah 3:10 . They carried on some commercial intercourse with it ( Isaiah 45:14 ).

Its inhabitants were descendants of Ham ( Genesis 10:6 ; Jeremiah 13:23 ; Isaiah 18:2 , "scattered and peeled," A.V.; but in RSV, "tall and smooth"). Herodotus, the Greek historian, describes them as "the tallest and handsomest of men." They are frequently represented on Egyptian monuments, and they are all of the type of the true negro. name: Raeye Children Aid Inc.
description:
Raeye Children Aid (RCA) is a non-profit organization that was established in 2016. RCA's mission is to empower children with intellectual and developmental disabilities through education. We accomplish this by providing access to education, vocational training and therapeutic programs for children of all ages. Through our powerful initiatives, we provide school supplies for children enrolled in Sibeste Negase and Agazian public schools located in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. With the help of RCA, students in these school districts receive new school uniforms, breakfast, and much needed school supplies. Our goal is to help the children develop the skills needed to succeed in school, obtain strong careers, and be active participants in their communities. 

Our Mission: RCA’s mission is to support children with intellectual and developmental disabilities by providing a therapeutic, exceptional, educational and vocational program to maximize their skills and increase independence.

name: Gebeta Maps
description:
Gebeta Maps is a provider of mapping and location-based services, headquartered in Ethiopia, Addis Ababa. The company was founded in 2021 by a team of experienced professionals in the field, with a mission to make accurate and reliable GIS and map-related services more accessible and affordable for individuals and businesses around the African space.

Our flagship offering is a suite of APIs that provide a range of mapping and location-based services, including geocoding, directions, matrix calculations, route optimization, and one-to-many calculations. Our APIs are easy to use and integrate with other software, making them a good choice for developers and businesses.

At Gebeta Maps, we use state-of-the-art mapping technology and data processing algorithms to create maps that are accurate, and we are constantly innovating to improve our services. Our team of experts work together to push the boundaries of what's possible with mapping and location technology.

name: Tehuti Waset Afnuit
description:
Ras-Tehuti, Hailing from a place not two far away, rarely gone four few...
They are All in One, Ras or RA's. The Creator of music that comes together to produce a masterpiece of sounds and expressions of Black Consciousness. Bass that pounds, beats that roar and arrangements that come from somewhere out of nowhere. 

Ras-Tehuti interlaces the cultural vibes of "old school" roots music all the way to "modern rhydms" that create a unique listening encounter. Songs that  has remixes, overdubbing and other musical refinements included, stand out
and stand strong. 

"12" is the title of their debut album which includes such classics as "Downfall of the Derg" in so...has a dark yet rejoicing feel of the title. "Wizdumb" includes the chanting and poetic blend of Bey and Tehuti, "Root" over laced with (Dr. Ben's) thoths and "Green Music" (FYAH). Were all Originally produced and released in Africa "Ethiopia" Adis Abeba" where they're roots grounded.

name: Ethiopian Gourmet Foods Company LLC
description:
Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.  New Orleans.  Asheville, NC.  Austin, TX.  These are the places our family has called home and the culinary environments which inspired our signature hot sauce.  We are two Ethiopian sisters, an American, and a whole lot of spices.  Our kitchen is always a mélange of food cultures:  Ethiopian meets Cajun Creole, Africa meets The South.  Every dish is a hybrid between the zest of the French Quarter, the sauces of Addis Ababa, the fresh hotness of Tex-Mex, and the tang of The Carolinas.  And it is in that spirit that we created The Original Ethiopian Hot Sauce™.  This is our way of sharing our love of our multicultural home cuisine with you. 

This hot sauce isn’t simply another boutique hot sauce to add to your collection in the pantry.  

Our hot sauce is an everyday, everywhere, every food kind of hot sauce.

name: NNHS Design
description:
We are Design & Visual Communications students from Newton North High School who have been given the opportunity by the Lemelson-MIT InvenTeam program to apply our design, science, technology, engineering and math skills to solve a real-world problem.

Our InvenTeam is producing a pedestrian alert system to be used in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. The system will warn drivers of crossing pedestrians and help pedestrians in developing countries safely cross dangerous roads. The invention will incorporate a dual-sensor method with a processing platform to calculate the arrival time of an oncoming vehicle.

To minimize environmental impact, we will build part of the system with recycled materials, and its entire power source will be solar energy. To implement the invention in a nonintrusive way, we will incorporate aesthetics of Ethiopian art and architecture.

name: Abeselom Yosef
description:
ሸንጎ (Shengo) is an Amharic term for council. In the past times and in some cases until 
present, the way our forefathers used to discuss and solve conflicts of different intensity 
levels which rise from the society through such traditional mediation platforms inspired 
and influenced us to name our institution after it.

Shengo Global, as an African think-tank institution witnesses unconstitutional acts, 
unresolved conflicts, and a rule of law at a question mark in most parts of Africa. To state these issues in an innovative way Shengo Global anchors peace, democracy, and good governance.

Shengo Global design the Shengo Panel with a vision to celebrate and share impacts.

Slogan- Impact matters
Therefore the scope of Shengo Global focuses on Seven thematic areas: Peace, Peace 
& Security, Governance, Diplomacy, Environment, Trade, and Law.
